 <H1>Find the age of the youngest sailor with age &#062 18, for each rating with at least 2 sailors (of any age)</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Shows HAVING clause can also contain a subquery.  
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Compare this with the query where we considered only ratings with 2 sailors over 18!
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>What if HAVING clause is replaced by:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>HAVING COUNT(*) &#0621</UL></UL></P>
<P><UL>
SELECT  S.rating,  MIN (S.age)
<BR></UL><UL>
FROM  Sailors S
</UL><UL>
WHERE  S.age &#062 18
</UL><UL>
GROUP BY  S.rating
</UL><UL>
HAVING  1  &#060  (SELECT  COUNT (*)
</UL><UL>
                         FROM  Sailors S2
</UL><UL>
                         WHERE  S.rating=S2.rating)</UL></P>
